                    Attendance Time
                </div>
                <div class="activity-details">
                    Welcome circle and check-in with each participant
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="activity-section">
                <div class="activity-title">
                    <div class="activity-number">3</div>
                    Activity Time
                </div>
                
                <div style="margin-bottom: 25px;">
                    <h4 style="color: #2d1674; margin-bottom: 10px;">🎯 Visual Tracking Activity</h4>
                    <div class="activity-details">
                        <strong>Setup:</strong> A large width line tape (brown or colored) is drawn on the floor, starting with a straight path that continues into a zigzag pattern creating a challenging course.<br><br>
                        <strong>Process:</strong> Each child is given a stick with a disc cone attached. With their parent's gentle assistance and guidance, the child must carefully track and follow the drawn line from start to finish, maintaining focus and coordination throughout the journey.<br><br>
                        <strong>Equipment:</strong> Large width line tape, Medicine ball, Green stick with disc cone
                    </div>
                    <div class="goals">
                        <div class="goals-title">Therapeutic Goals & Benefits:</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Hand-Eye Coordination:</strong> Develops precise visual-motor integration as children learn to coordinate what they see with their hand movements</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Body Balance:</strong> Strengthens core stability and proprioceptive awareness while navigating the path</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Visual Processing:</strong> Enhances visual tracking skills and spatial awareness</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Focus & Attention:</strong> Improves sustained attention and concentration abilities</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div>
                    <h4 style="color: #2d1674; margin-bottom: 10px;">👣 Point-to-Point Foot Coordination</h4>
                    <div class="activity-details">
                        <strong>Setup:</strong> Plastic glasses are arranged in a straight line with colorful sponge balls placed alternately beside each glass, creating an engaging obstacle course.<br><br>
                        <strong>Process:</strong> Children use their feet to carefully pick up each sponge ball and drop it into the corresponding glass. Parents provide supportive assistance throughout, encouraging and guiding their child's movements while celebrating each successful attempt.<br><br>
                        <strong>Equipment:</strong> Colorful sponge balls, Plastic glasses
                    </div>
                    <div class="goals">
                        <div class="goals-title">Therapeutic Goals & Benefits:</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Foot Grasping Skills:</strong> Develops fine motor control in the feet and toes, strengthening intrinsic foot muscles</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Foot-Eye Coordination:</strong> Enhances the connection between visual input and lower extremity motor output</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Body Balance & Stability:</strong> Improves single-leg stance and dynamic balance while performing the task</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Self-Confidence:</strong> Builds self-esteem through successful task completion and positive reinforcement</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Bilateral Coordination:</strong> Develops coordination between both sides of the body</div>
                        <div class="goal-item"><strong>Problem-Solving:</strong> Encourages strategic thinking and motor planning skills</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="activity-section">
                <div class="activity-title">
                    <div class="activity-number">4</div>
                    Rhyme Time
                </div>
                <div class="rhyme-section">
                    <div class="rhyme-text">"Animal in the Jungle and Nobody Around"</div>
                    <div style="color: #2d1674; margin: 15px 0; font-size: 1rem; line-height: 1.6;">
                        <strong>How it Works:</strong> Children sing the base song "Nobody Around" (repeated 4 times), then we replace "animal" with specific animals to create variations and encourage participation, memory, and language development.
                    </div>
                    <div class="rhyme-text">🎵 Nobody Around (x4) 🎵</div>
                    <div class="animal-list">
                        <div class="animal-item">🦁 Lion</div>
                        <div class="animal-item">🐅 Tiger</div>
                        <div class="animal-item">🐴 Horse</div>
                    </div>
                    <div style="color: #e17090; margin-top: 15px; font-weight: bold; font-size: 0.9rem;">
                        <strong>Benefits:</strong> Enhances memory, language skills, rhythm awareness, and group participation
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
